.TH "NAVIGATEEVENT.SOURCEELEMENT" "3JS" "December 9, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigateEvent.sourceElement \- NavigateEvent: sourceElement property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]sourceElement\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]NavigateEvent\f[R] interface returns an \f[CR]Element\f[R] object
representing the initiating element, in cases where the navigation was
initiated by an element.
.PP
The initiating element can be:
.IP \(bu 2
An HTML \f[CR]<a>\f[R] element (or SVG \f[CR]<a>\f[R] element).
.IP \(bu 2
An \f[CR]<area>\f[R] element.
.IP \(bu 2
A submit button (\f[CR]<input type=\(dqsubmit\(dq>\f[R] or
\f[CR]<button type=\(dqsubmit\(dq>\f[R]).
.IP \(bu 2
A submitted \f[CR]<form>\f[R] element.
.SH VALUE
An \f[CR]Element\f[R] object representing the element that initiated the
navigation, or \f[CR]null\f[R] if the navigation was not initiated by an
element.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Getting the \f[CR]sourceElement\f[R] for an event
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqnavigate\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(event.sourceElement);
});
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
